com.freebase.api
Class Freebase

java.lang.Object
  com.freebase.api.Freebase

public class Freebase
extends Object

This class is the main access point to the Freebase API. You can obtain two flavors of this class, one that operates on freebase.com and one that operates on sandbox-freebase.com. sandbox-freebase.com is a scratch system that works exactly like freebase.com but its data get reset every week and brought back in synch with freebase.com. If your programs write data in Freebase, we highly encourage to use sandbox first for extensive testing before turning the writes over to Freebase.com. Use Freebase.getFreebase() to obtain a instance of this class that talks to freebase.com and Freebase.getFreebaseSandbox() to obtain one that talks to sandbox-freebase.com.

sign_in

public void sign_in(String username,
                    String password)
For API calls that write data in Freebase, your requests must be authenticated. Calling this method with your Freebase username and password will provide enough credentials for your write API calls to be authorized. NOTE: if you don't have a Freebase account, you can get one for free at freebase.com
